channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Filings in Federal Tax Case Claim Hunter Biden Was Paid by Romanian Oligarch to Get Investigation Killed
'Great asset': Radical Dems, socialists thrilled by Harris’ VP pick Tim Walz
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris' pick of Gov. Tim Walz as her VP was greeted with relief and delight from hardline Democrats and socialists, who saw it as a boost to their efforts.

item.title: Microsoft: Iranian Hackers Target US Election
item.description: Iran is accelerating online activity that appears intended to influence the U.S. election, in one case targeting a presidential campaign with an email phishing attack, Microsoft said Friday.

item.title: Camping World Proudly Flies Huge US Flag Despite CA Officials Demanding They Take It Down
Progressive women's groups silent on second gentleman Doug Emhoff's affair
item.description: Progressive women's groups, including EMILYs List, did not respond to Fox News Digital's inquiry about second gentleman Doug Emhoff's past affair affecting his image as a leader.

item.title: Trump Targets Sen. Jon Tester in Montana Rally
item.description: With control of the Senate potentially at stake, former President Donald Trump is visiting Montana on Friday hoping to remedy some unfinished business from 2018, when he campaigned in Big Sky Country in a bid to oust incumbent Democrat Sen. Jon Tester. Tester has tried to...

item.title: Ukraine's Surprise Invasion of Russia Leaves Putin With the Stunned-Mullet Look
Minnesota riots continued after Walz took ‘responsibility to ensure’ there wouldn’t be chaos
item.description: Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz claimed "responsibility to ensure" riots in Minneapolis would be curbed in 2020 after the death of George Floyd during an interaction with police.

item.title: Rep. Comer to Newsmax: Walz 'Perfect Candidate' for China
item.description: Rep. James Comer, R-Ky., told Newsmax on Thursday he's concerned about Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz, the Democrat nominee for vice president, and his ties to China.

item.title: Reporters Finally Corner Harris for Questions, but She Once Again Illustrates Trump's Point
Walz pick does little to persuade Dearborn’s anti-Biden/Harris voters
item.description: Vice President Harris' decision to tap Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz as running mate has not tipped the scales in her favor among Arab-American voters in Dearborn, Michigan.

item.title: Elder, Leavitt to Newsmax: Dems Fearmongering to Get Votes
item.description: Larry Elder and press secretary for former President Donald Trump Karoline Leavitt told Newsmax on Thursday that all Democrats are doing is fearmongering to get votes when they claim former President Donald Trump and Republicans will put an end to Social Security.

item.title: Mexico Refuses to Poke the Bear, Denies Ukraine's Request to Arrest Vladimir Putin
Kamala Harris finally fields questions from press after dodging media for 18 days since becoming Dem nominee
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris fielded questions from the media for the first time since becoming the Democratic nominee for president after facing criticism.

item.title: Ric Grenell to Newsmax: Arab Americans Shouldn't Back Harris
item.description: Ric Grenell, former acting director of national intelligence during the Trump administration, told Newsmax on Thursday that Arab Americans shouldn't support Vice President Kamala Harris, the Democrat presidential nominee.
